Written to `/data/swarm/docs/reviews/r9-sec-summary.md`.

The summary covers all 10 requested topics:

- **Attack surface** —4 external entry points, internal coms via Unix sockets/NATS, backend services unexposed
- **Sandbox boundaries** — 3 enforcement layers: OS (secomp + cgroup v2 + no network namespace), Wasmtime (fuel, memory, epoch kill, WASI-off), and lifecycle (per-tick fork+kill)
- **Auth model** — OAuth2 → Ed25519 short certs (24h) → 15min JWT scopes; player_id is server-injected and cannot be self-reported
- **Source gate** — First stage of the command pipeline; only `WASM` source produces gameplay commands; `MCP_Deploy` is hard-rejected (403) at this gate
- **WASM isolation** — Deferred command model means no mutating host functions exist; 4 read-only host functions with per-call fuel costs and per-tick call caps
- **Fuel refund** — 50% refund for 3 race-condition rejection reasons only; refund applies next-tick only; module hash binding prevents cross-deploy credit transfer; auto-throttle at >80% rate over 3 ticks
- **Prompt injection defense** — Input charset restriction + `"untrusted": true` field tagging + SDK delimiter contract using characters outside the allowed player charset
- **MCP security contract** — Read/deploy/debug only; no game-action tools exist; full transport security spec; 90-day immutable audit log in ClickHouse
- **Replay privacy** — 4-tier `replay_privacy` enum; Arena forces public after ≥100 tick delay; spectators see physical state only, never internal player data; single visibility cache prevents cross-surface leaks
- **RuleMod capabilities** — Limited to6 `actions` API calls; no arbitrary attribute writes; 100ms/10k-AST-node execution budget; auto-disable after 10 consecutive over-limit ticks

Also included 5 open questions flaged for deeper review (Rhai flag whitelist scope, Rollback dual-person enforcement mechanism, module cache + ban interaction, spectate constraint enforcement point, simulate isolation model).
